<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="679" data-end="744"><div class="contain-inline-size rounded-2xl corner-superellipse/1.1 relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary"><div class="flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary select-none rounded-t-2xl corner-t-superellipse/1.1">latex</div><div class="sticky top-[calc(--spacing(9)+var(--header-height))] @w-xl/main:top-9"><div class="absolute end-0 bottom-0 flex h-9 items-center pe-2"><div class="bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary text-token-text-secondary flex items-center gap-4 rounded-sm px-2 font-sans text-xs"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-1" aria-label="Copy"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-k5zux585.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Copy code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-latex"><span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\usepackage</span></span><span>[T1]{fontenc}
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\usepackage</span></span><span>[utf8]{inputenc}
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="746" data-end="779">Your preamble should now include:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="781" data-end="846"><div class="contain-inline-size rounded-2xl corner-superellipse/1.1 relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary"><div class="flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary select-none rounded-t-2xl corner-t-superellipse/1.1">latex</div><div class="sticky top-[calc(--spacing(9)+var(--header-height))] @w-xl/main:top-9"><div class="absolute end-0 bottom-0 flex h-9 items-center pe-2"><div class="bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary text-token-text-secondary flex items-center gap-4 rounded-sm px-2 font-sans text-xs"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-1" aria-label="Copy"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-k5zux585.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Copy code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-latex"><span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\usepackage</span></span><span>[T1]{fontenc}
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\usepackage</span></span><span>[utf8]{inputenc}
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="848" data-end="865">This tells LaTeX:</p>
<ul data-start="866" data-end="943">
<li data-start="866" data-end="889">
<p data-start="868" data-end="889">“The source is UTF-8”</p>
</li>
<li data-start="890" data-end="943">
<p data-start="892" data-end="943">“Use fonts that actually contain curly punctuation”</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="945" data-end="1022">✔ Your smart apostrophe will render correctly<br data-start="990" data-end="993">
✔ No need to change your text</p>
<hr data-start="1024" data-end="1027">
<h3 data-start="1029" data-end="1092"><strong data-start="1033" data-end="1092">Option 2 (most robust, modern): use LuaLaTeX or XeLaTeX</strong></h3>
<p data-start="1094" data-end="1166">If you compile with <strong data-start="1114" data-end="1126">LuaLaTeX</strong> or <strong data-start="1130" data-end="1141">XeLaTeX</strong>, Unicode works natively.</p>
<p data-start="1168" data-end="1219">Then remove <code data-start="1180" data-end="1190">inputenc</code> entirely and optionally add:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="1221" data-end="1255"><div class="contain-inline-size rounded-2xl corner-superellipse/1.1 relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary"><div class="flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary select-none rounded-t-2xl corner-t-superellipse/1.1">latex</div><div class="sticky top-[calc(--spacing(9)+var(--header-height))] @w-xl/main:top-9"><div class="absolute end-0 bottom-0 flex h-9 items-center pe-2"><div class="bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary text-token-text-secondary flex items-center gap-4 rounded-sm px-2 font-sans text-xs"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-1" aria-label="Copy"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-k5zux585.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Copy code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-latex"><span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\usepackage</span></span><span>{fontspec}
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="1257" data-end="1358">✔ Best Unicode support<br data-start="1279" data-end="1282">
✔ Best for long-form modern prose<br data-start="1315" data-end="1318">
✔ Recommended if your editor supports it</p>
<hr data-start="1360" data-end="1363">
<h3 data-start="1365" data-end="1425"><strong data-start="1369" data-end="1425">Option 3 (manual, old-school): replace the character</strong></h3>
<p data-start="1427" data-end="1435">Replace:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="1437" data-end="1458"><div class="contain-inline-size rounded-2xl corner-superellipse/1.1 relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary"><div class="flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary select-none rounded-t-2xl corner-t-superellipse/1.1"></div><div class="sticky top-[calc(--spacing(9)+var(--header-height))] @w-xl/main:top-9"><div class="absolute end-0 bottom-0 flex h-9 items-center pe-2"><div class="bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary text-token-text-secondary flex items-center gap-4 rounded-sm px-2 font-sans text-xs"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-1" aria-label="Copy"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-k5zux585.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Copy code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre!"><span><span>Author’s Note
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="1460" data-end="1465">with:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="1467" data-end="1493"><div class="contain-inline-size rounded-2xl corner-superellipse/1.1 relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary"><div class="flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary select-none rounded-t-2xl corner-t-superellipse/1.1">latex</div><div class="sticky top-[calc(--spacing(9)+var(--header-height))] @w-xl/main:top-9"><div class="absolute end-0 bottom-0 flex h-9 items-center pe-2"><div class="bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary text-token-text-secondary flex items-center gap-4 rounded-sm px-2 font-sans text-xs"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-1" aria-label="Copy"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-k5zux585.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Copy code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-latex"><span><span>Author's Note
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="1495" data-end="1575">This uses ASCII <code data-start="1511" data-end="1514">'</code> and will <em data-start="1524" data-end="1532">always</em> work—but you lose typographic correctness.</p>
<hr data-start="1577" data-end="1580">
<h2 data-start="1582" data-end="1641">🧠 Why this is happening specifically in <em data-start="1626" data-end="1632">your</em> document</h2>
<p data-start="1643" data-end="1656">You’re using:</p>
<ul data-start="1658" data-end="1739">
<li data-start="1658" data-end="1701">
<p data-start="1660" data-end="1701">UTF-8 text (smart punctuation, em-dashes)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1702" data-end="1719">
<p data-start="1704" data-end="1719"><code data-start="1704" data-end="1713">article</code> class</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1720" data-end="1739">
<p data-start="1722" data-end="1739">pdfLaTeX defaults</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1741" data-end="1867">Your em-dashes work because they’re likely <code data-start="1784" data-end="1787">—</code> mapped by your editor or converted, but <strong data-start="1828" data-end="1866">curly apostrophes are more fragile</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="1869" data-end="1922">Adding <code data-start="1876" data-end="1885">fontenc</code> + <code data-start="1888" data-end="1898">inputenc</code> resolves <em data-start="1908" data-end="1913">all</em> of this.</p>
<hr data-start="1924" data-end="1927">
<h2 data-start="1929" data-end="1983">✅ Final recommended preamble (clean + future-proof)</h2>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="1985" data-end="2229"><div class="contain-inline-size rounded-2xl corner-superellipse/1.1 relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary"><div class="flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary select-none rounded-t-2xl corner-t-superellipse/1.1">latex</div><div class="sticky top-[calc(--spacing(9)+var(--header-height))] @w-xl/main:top-9"><div class="absolute end-0 bottom-0 flex h-9 items-center pe-2"><div class="bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary text-token-text-secondary flex items-center gap-4 rounded-sm px-2 font-sans text-xs"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-1" aria-label="Copy"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-k5zux585.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Copy code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-latex"><span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">\documentclass</span></span><span>[12pt]{article}

