</li>
<li data-start="2295" data-end="2319">
<p data-start="2297" data-end="2319">Improve PDF copy/paste</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="2321" data-end="2324">
<h2 data-start="2326" data-end="2369">Very Wittgensteinian footnote (optional)</h2>
<p data-start="2371" data-end="2526">There’s something almost too perfect here:<br data-start="2413" data-end="2416">
the apostrophe <em data-start="2431" data-end="2441">vanishes</em> because LaTeX doesn’t know how to <strong data-start="2476" data-end="2483">say</strong> it without being taught how to <strong data-start="2515" data-end="2522">see</strong> it.</p>
<p data-start="2528" data-end="2583">Once you clarify the conditions, the mark shows itself.</p>
<p data-start="2585" data-end="2602">If you want next:</p>
<ul data-start="2603" data-end="2730">
<li data-start="2603" data-end="2649">
